[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":909},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F02\u002Ffix-vue-mustache-flicker-with-v-cloak\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F02\u002Ffix-vue-mustache-flicker-with-v-cloak\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F02\u002Ffix-vue-mustache-flicker-with-v-cloak\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F02\u002Ffix-vue-mustache-flicker-with-v-cloak\u002F":885,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F02\u002Ffix-vue-mustache-flicker-with-v-cloak\u002F":894},"\u002Fvue\u002F20221202\u002F2131448011\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":868,"date":869,"description":870,"extension":871,"lang":872,"meta":873,"navigation":596,"path":874,"readingMinutes":717,"seo":875,"standalone":876,"stem":877,"tags":878,"tldr":882,"updated":869,"url":883,"__hash__":884},"content\u002Fen\u002FVue\u002Ffix-vue-mustache-flicker-with-v-cloak.md","Fix the Vue Mustache Flicker With v-cloak","8403112114",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":859},"minimark",[11,16,25,32,35,42,45,52,56,67,78,81,87,90,96,102,105,110,117,119,125,236,239,276,279,284,298,301,310,344,355,369,379,383,392,474,828,831,835,839,855],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19,20,24],"p",{},"Sometimes a slow network makes Vue render late, and you briefly see the raw Mustache (",[21,22,23],"code",{},"{{ }}",") syntax on the page. Not a great look — so here's a quick note on how to fix it.",[12,26,28,29,31],{"id":27},"what-causes-the-mustache-to-show","What causes the Mustache (",[21,30,23],{},") to show",[17,33,34],{},"It's actually an interesting issue. Under normal conditions you'd rarely see this:",[17,36,37],{},[38,39],"img",{"alt":40,"src":41},"Mustache showing before Vue instances","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-12-02%2016.42.32.png",[17,43,44],{},"What's happening? The main cause is that the network is slow enough that Vue's JavaScript file hasn't finished downloading yet.",[17,46,47,48,51],{},"Normally the HTML file downloads first, so you see the HTML content first. As the browser starts rendering the HTML from top to bottom and hits a ",[21,49,50],{},"\u003Cscript>"," tag, it starts downloading the JavaScript file. Once that file downloads, it starts executing. That's the basic rendering flow.",[12,53,55],{"id":54},"how-to-reproduce-it","How to reproduce it",[17,57,58,59,66],{},"Reproducing this is easy. Here's a ",[60,61,65],"a",{"href":62,"rel":63},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FPopawrR?editors=1010",[64],"nofollow","CodePen"," sample — try throttling your network speed and watch what happens.",[68,69,77],"iframe",{"height":70,"style":71,"scrolling":72,"title":73,"src":74,"frameBorder":72,"loading":75,"allowTransparency":76,"allowFullScreen":76},300,"width: 100%;","no","Vue3 Composition API","https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fembed\u002FPopawrR?default-tab=html%2Cresult","lazy","true","\n  See the Pen \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FPopawrR\">\n  Vue3 Composition API\u003C\u002Fa> by Ray (\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\">@hsiangfeng\u003C\u002Fa>)\n  on \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\">CodePen\u003C\u002Fa>.\n",[17,79,80],{},"In Firefox, the throttling option is here:",[17,82,83],{},[38,84],{"alt":85,"src":86},"Network","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-12-02%2016.51.19.png",[17,88,89],{},"In the dropdown, pick your network speed:",[17,91,92],{},[38,93],{"alt":94,"src":95},"Speed","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-12-02%2016.51.26.png",[17,97,98,99,101],{},"Pick \"2G Good\" or \"3G Good\", reload the CodePen, and you'll see the Mustache (",[21,100,23],{},") flicker.",[17,103,104],{},"Chrome's option is in the same place too:",[17,106,107],{},[38,108],{"alt":85,"src":109},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-12-02%2016.53.34.png",[17,111,112,113,116],{},"To fix this, we use Vue's ",[21,114,115],{},"v-cloak"," directive.",[12,118,115],{"id":115},[17,120,121,122,124],{},"The fix is super simple — just add ",[21,123,115],{}," to the tag:",[126,127,132],"pre",{"className":128,"code":129,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"language-html shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","\u003Cdiv id=\"app\">\n  \u003Cp v-cloak>\n    My name is: {{ myName }}\n  \u003C\u002Fp>\n  \u003Cbr>\n  \u003Cinput type=\"text\" v-model=\"myName\">\n\u003C\u002Fdiv>\n","html","",[21,133,134,161,174,180,190,200,226],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,136,139,143,147,151,154,158],"span",{"class":137,"line":138},"line",1,[135,140,142],{"class":141},"s8XSl","\u003C",[135,144,146],{"class":145},"syv7_","div",[135,148,150],{"class":149},"sK3KL"," id",[135,152,153],{"class":141},"=",[135,155,157],{"class":156},"sWayO","\"app\"",[135,159,160],{"class":141},">\n",[135,162,164,167,169,172],{"class":137,"line":163},2,[135,165,166],{"class":141},"  \u003C",[135,168,17],{"class":145},[135,170,171],{"class":149}," v-cloak",[135,173,160],{"class":141},[135,175,177],{"class":137,"line":176},3,[135,178,179],{"class":141},"    My name is: {{ myName }}\n",[135,181,183,186,188],{"class":137,"line":182},4,[135,184,185],{"class":141},"  \u003C\u002F",[135,187,17],{"class":145},[135,189,160],{"class":141},[135,191,193,195,198],{"class":137,"line":192},5,[135,194,166],{"class":141},[135,196,197],{"class":145},"br",[135,199,160],{"class":141},[135,201,203,205,208,211,213,216,219,221,224],{"class":137,"line":202},6,[135,204,166],{"class":141},[135,206,207],{"class":145},"input",[135,209,210],{"class":149}," type",[135,212,153],{"class":141},[135,214,215],{"class":156},"\"text\"",[135,217,218],{"class":149}," v-model",[135,220,153],{"class":141},[135,222,223],{"class":156},"\"myName\"",[135,225,160],{"class":141},[135,227,229,232,234],{"class":137,"line":228},7,[135,230,231],{"class":141},"\u003C\u002F",[135,233,146],{"class":145},[135,235,160],{"class":141},[17,237,238],{},"Then add a little CSS:",[126,240,244],{"className":241,"code":242,"language":243,"meta":131,"style":131},"language-css shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","[v-cloak] {\n  display: none;\n}\n","css",[21,245,246,256,271],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,247,248,251,253],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,249,250],{"class":141},"[",[135,252,115],{"class":149},[135,254,255],{"class":141},"] {\n",[135,257,258,262,265,268],{"class":137,"line":163},[135,259,261],{"class":260},"stw71","  display",[135,263,264],{"class":141},": ",[135,266,267],{"class":260},"none",[135,269,270],{"class":141},";\n",[135,272,273],{"class":137,"line":176},[135,274,275],{"class":141},"}\n",[17,277,278],{},"Done.",[68,280,283],{"height":70,"style":71,"scrolling":72,"title":281,"src":282,"frameBorder":72,"loading":75,"allowTransparency":76,"allowFullScreen":76},"v-cloak example","https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fembed\u002FyLERxRY?default-tab=html%2Cresult","\n  See the Pen \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FyLERxRY\">\n  v-cloak example\u003C\u002Fa> by Ray (\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\">@hsiangfeng\u003C\u002Fa>)\n  on \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\">CodePen\u003C\u002Fa>.\n",[17,285,286,287,290,291,293,294,297],{},"But you'll notice this approach is slightly silly — to hide a simple piece of text, you're forced to wrap it in a tag like ",[21,288,289],{},"\u003Cp>",", which makes the HTML uglier. You can actually put ",[21,292,115],{}," directly on ",[21,295,296],{},"#app"," to get the same effect.",[17,299,300],{},"Now you might wonder:",[17,302,303,304,306,307,309],{},"\"Is ",[21,305,115],{}," a Vue directive? Earlier you said the rendering is slow because Vue hasn't loaded yet — so how can ",[21,308,115],{}," even work?\"",[17,311,312,313,316,317,320,321,323,324,327,328,330,331,333,334,336,337,339,340,343],{},"Right — it is a Vue directive. But the underlying mechanism is just CSS's ",[21,314,315],{},"display: none",". That property hides the element on the page. Then you use the CSS selector ",[21,318,319],{},"[v-cloak]"," to target all elements with the ",[21,322,115],{}," attribute and set their ",[21,325,326],{},"display"," to ",[21,329,267],{},". Once Vue finishes loading, it automatically removes ",[21,332,115],{}," and the element becomes visible. So you can call it a Vue directive, but really it's just CSS's ",[21,335,315],{}," doing the work — the attribute just has to be ",[21,338,115],{},", not ",[21,341,342],{},"v-hide"," or something else.",[17,345,346,348,349,354],{},[21,347,115],{}," is also covered in the Vue ",[60,350,353],{"href":351,"rel":352},"https:\u002F\u002Fcn.vuejs.org\u002Fapi\u002Fbuilt-in-directives.html#v-cloak",[64],"official docs",". Here's part of the description:",[356,357,358],"blockquote",{},[17,359,360,361,364,365,368],{},"Used to hide un-compiled template until it is ready.\nWhen using in-DOM templates, there may be a \"flash of un-compiled templates\": the user may see raw mustache tags until the mounted component replaces them with rendered content.\nv-cloak will remain on the element until the associated component instance is mounted. Combined with CSS rules such as ",[21,362,363],{},"[v-cloak] { display: none }",", it can be used to hide the raw templates until the component is ready.\nUntil compile finishes, the ",[21,366,367],{},"\u003Cdiv>"," will not be visible.",[17,370,371,372,375,376,378],{},"If you're wondering whether ",[21,373,374],{},"v-if"," could solve this — no, it can't. ",[21,377,374],{}," also needs Vue to finish loading before it can run.",[12,380,382],{"id":381},"improving-v-cloak","Improving v-cloak",[17,384,385,386,388,389,391],{},"Using ",[21,387,315],{}," for ",[21,390,115],{}," works, but it leaves you with a blank screen — bad UX. You can write a little CSS loader so the user at least sees something while Vue loads. Here's a simple version:",[126,393,395],{"className":128,"code":394,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"\u003Cdiv id=\"app\" v-cloak>\n  My name is: {{ myName }}\n  \u003Cbr>\n  \u003Cinput type=\"text\" v-model=\"myName\">\n\u003C\u002Fdiv>\n\u003Cdiv id=\"loader\">\u003C\u002Fdiv>\n",[21,396,397,413,418,426,446,454],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,398,399,401,403,405,407,409,411],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,400,142],{"class":141},[135,402,146],{"class":145},[135,404,150],{"class":149},[135,406,153],{"class":141},[135,408,157],{"class":156},[135,410,171],{"class":149},[135,412,160],{"class":141},[135,414,415],{"class":137,"line":163},[135,416,417],{"class":141},"  My name is: {{ myName }}\n",[135,419,420,422,424],{"class":137,"line":176},[135,421,166],{"class":141},[135,423,197],{"class":145},[135,425,160],{"class":141},[135,427,428,430,432,434,436,438,440,442,444],{"class":137,"line":182},[135,429,166],{"class":141},[135,431,207],{"class":145},[135,433,210],{"class":149},[135,435,153],{"class":141},[135,437,215],{"class":156},[135,439,218],{"class":149},[135,441,153],{"class":141},[135,443,223],{"class":156},[135,445,160],{"class":141},[135,447,448,450,452],{"class":137,"line":192},[135,449,231],{"class":141},[135,451,146],{"class":145},[135,453,160],{"class":141},[135,455,456,458,460,462,464,467,470,472],{"class":137,"line":202},[135,457,142],{"class":141},[135,459,146],{"class":145},[135,461,150],{"class":149},[135,463,153],{"class":141},[135,465,466],{"class":156},"\"loader\"",[135,468,469],{"class":141},">\u003C\u002F",[135,471,146],{"class":145},[135,473,160],{"class":141},[126,475,477],{"className":241,"code":476,"language":243,"meta":131,"style":131},"[v-cloak] + #loader {\n  position: fixed;\n  top: 0;\n  left: 0;\n  width: 100%;\n  height: 100%;\n  background: #fff;\n  z-index: 9999;\n}\n\n[v-cloak] + #loader:before {\n  content: '';\n  position: absolute;\n  top: 50%;\n  left: 50%;\n  width: 50px;\n  height: 50px;\n  border-radius: 50%;\n  border: 3px solid #ccc;\n  border-top-color: #333;\n  animation: spin 1s linear infinite;\n}\n\n@keyframes spin {\n  to {\n    transform: rotate(360deg);\n  }\n}\n",[21,478,479,498,510,522,533,548,561,573,586,591,598,614,627,639,653,666,680,693,707,728,741,764,769,774,786,794,817,823],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,480,481,483,485,488,492,495],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,482,250],{"class":141},[135,484,115],{"class":149},[135,486,487],{"class":141},"] ",[135,489,491],{"class":490},"sOudu","+",[135,493,494],{"class":149}," #loader",[135,496,497],{"class":141}," {\n",[135,499,500,503,505,508],{"class":137,"line":163},[135,501,502],{"class":260},"  position",[135,504,264],{"class":141},[135,506,507],{"class":260},"fixed",[135,509,270],{"class":141},[135,511,512,515,517,520],{"class":137,"line":176},[135,513,514],{"class":260},"  top",[135,516,264],{"class":141},[135,518,519],{"class":260},"0",[135,521,270],{"class":141},[135,523,524,527,529,531],{"class":137,"line":182},[135,525,526],{"class":260},"  left",[135,528,264],{"class":141},[135,530,519],{"class":260},[135,532,270],{"class":141},[135,534,535,538,540,543,546],{"class":137,"line":192},[135,536,537],{"class":260},"  width",[135,539,264],{"class":141},[135,541,542],{"class":260},"100",[135,544,545],{"class":490},"%",[135,547,270],{"class":141},[135,549,550,553,555,557,559],{"class":137,"line":202},[135,551,552],{"class":260},"  height",[135,554,264],{"class":141},[135,556,542],{"class":260},[135,558,545],{"class":490},[135,560,270],{"class":141},[135,562,563,566,568,571],{"class":137,"line":228},[135,564,565],{"class":260},"  background",[135,567,264],{"class":141},[135,569,570],{"class":260},"#fff",[135,572,270],{"class":141},[135,574,576,579,581,584],{"class":137,"line":575},8,[135,577,578],{"class":260},"  z-inde